<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-10-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-10-02"><hi rend="italic">October 2,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 37.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On Wednesday evening, September 29,
                            ultimo, the Spanish ministry tendered their resignations to the Queen
                            Regent.</p>
                        <p>I withhold comment until a new ministry shall have been announced.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>